A baby girl has died after suffering a ‘medical episode’ at nursery. The emergency services were called to Tiny Toes Children’s Day Nursery, in Stockport, on Monday. An eight-month-old girl was rushed to hospital but was later pronounced dead. Her death is being treated as unexplained. Franck Pelle, owner of Tiny Toes Children’s Day Nursery, told the Manchester Evening News: ‘Our heartfelt condolences and deepest sorrow are with the parents and family at this devastating time. ‘We are working closely with all involved to assist and due to the sensitivities and ongoing investigation we are unable to comment any further at this time.’ A spokesperson for Greater Manchester Police confirmed officers were called by ‘colleagues from North West Ambulance Service to a report of a child suffering a medical episode’ at the nursery shortly before 3.20pm on Monday. ‘An eight-month-old girl was taken to hospital where she sadly died,’ the force said. ‘The death is currently being treated as unexplained and an investigation to establish the cause is on-going.’ Following the tragedy, Ofsted said it had ‘suspended this setting to allow time for other agencies to complete their enquiries’ while the investigation into what happened takes place. A spokesperson for Stockport Council added: ‘The council is aware of the sad news of the death of an eight-month-old girl at a premises on Mellor Road in Cheadle. ‘First and foremost, our thoughts go out to the family for their loss at this difficult time. We are not able to comment any further and await the outcome of the investigation.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page. 